==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homogenous
<hw>Ho*mog"e*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Having a resemblance in structure, due to descent from a common
progenitor with subsequent modification; homogenetic; -- applied both to
animals and plants. See <er>Homoplastic</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homogeny</ent>⟦br⟧
